name: Wrap Full Hyper
description: A Wrap Full that lands in hyper.

name: Cheat 720 Shuriken
description: A Cheat 720 that lands on the kicking leg in true hyper (TKT) / mega stance.

name: Raiz
description: The Raiz can be thought of as a “no-handed” Gumbi or a laid-back / arched Tornado.  Can be pronounced “rise” or “raise” or “high-eeze” (Portuguese)

name: Tak Double Full Touchdown
description: A Tak Double Full that touches down like a Touchdown Raiz at the end.

name: Corkscrew Wackknife
description: A Corkscrew that finishes with a Wackknife.

name: Double Gainer
description: A Gainer Tuck with two flips.  First landed by Vellu in February, 2011.

name: Crowd Awakener
description: A Tornado with a split kick / straddle.

name: Butterfly Twist Round
description: A Butterfly Twist with a round kick executed before landing.

name: Gainer Switch
description: A Gainer Flash that switches legs and lands on the plant leg again. The current Gainer Switch record is held by Ilya Vtorin at 25 Gainer Switches.

name: Butterfly Kick Terada Grab
description: A Butter Knife where the hook kick leg is grabbed before kicking.

name: Aerial Sidewinder
description: An Aerial where the outside leg initiates an extra twist while in an outstretched, arched position, making this an Aerial Twist variation.

name: Spyder Twist
description: A Spyder with an extra in-air spin executed before landing.

name: Gainer Switch Half
description: A Gainer Switch that rotates an extra 180° before landing.

name: Gainer Sidewinder
description: A Gainer with a Sidewinder – this pulls it all the way back to complete, making this a corkscrew variation.

name: Full McDirty
description: A Full Feilong with an extra twist before landing.

name: Popcorn
description: A Full Doubleleg that is executed in a piked position the entire way.

name: Swing 900 Knife
description: A vert kick that swings and leaves the ground in (roughly) backside, spins (roughly) 540° and executes a knife.

name: Full Tai Fighter
description: A Full Twist with a Tai-Fighter.

name: Rodeo Corkscrew
description: A Corkscrew with a leg grab and an arched back.

name: Cheat 1260 Doubleleg
description: A Cheat 1260 that finishes with a parafuso/doubleleg.

name: Kaydem
description: A Blasterscoot with no hands.

name: Butterfly Kick
description: A move with Wushu origins. The Butterfly Kick forms the basis of the Butterfly Twist and all the variations that follow.

name: Ironman Full Snapu
description: An Ironman Full that finishes with a Snapu.

name: Rodeo Corkscrew Shuriken Cutter
description: A Shuriken Cutter with a Rodeo leg grab.

name: Butterfly Twist Doubleleg Twist
description: A Butterfly Twist Doubleleg with an extra twist executed after the Doubleleg before landing.

name: Corkscrew Snapu
description: A Corkscrew that finishes with a snapu. Making this a double corkscrew variation.

name: Gumbi
description: The base for all Raiz-type of tricks. Can be thought of as an arched, opposite-side cartwheel.

name: Wrap Full Swipeknife
description: A Wrap Full that finishes with a Swipeknife.

name: Arabian X-Out
description: An Arabian that finishes with an X-Out / Straddle.

name: Wackknife Turbo
description: A Wackknife that lands in frontside on both legs (turbo).

name: Aerial Twist
description: An Aerial with a twist, landing in complete. Can be thought of as an inverted Butterfly Twist.

name: Cheat 720 Twist Round
description: A Cheat 720 Twist with a round kick executed before landing. Can be thought of as a “laid back” Cheat 900.

name: Aerial Twist Gumbi
description: An Aerial Twist combined with a Gumbi.

name: Back-In Squirrel-Out
description: A Back Tuck followed by a Squirrel Backflip (two flips).

name: Rocketboi Round
description: A Rocketboi with a round kick executed before landing.

name: Double Full Swipeknife
description: A Double Full that finishes with a Swipeknife. Could be thought of as an inverted Backside 1260 Knife.

name: Donut Boy
description: Could be thought of as a Corkscrew Lonestar.

name: Tak Full Hyperhook
description: A Tak Full that finishes with a hyperhook.

name: Grand Master Arabian
description: A GMS that finishes with a front flip.

name: Pop 540
description: A Pop Tornado that lands in hyper stance and on the kicking leg.

name: Dragonfly Boxcutter
description: A Dragonfly Corkscrew that finishes with a hyperhook.

name: Double Layout
description: A Layout with 2 flips.

name: Tornado Double
description: A Tornado with two round kicks executed before landing.

name: Cheat Double Hook
description: An upright Spyder with an extra hook. Could be thought of as a precursor to the Wackknife.

name: Aerial
description: A Cartwheel with no-hands. Unlike the gymnast version of the Aerial, the Tricker/Butterfly Aerial goes side to side.

name: Gainer Helicoptero
description: A Gainer that finishes with a helicoptero.

name: Full Hyper
description: A Full Twist that lands in hyper stance.

name: Butterfly Twist Twist-Kick
description: A Butterfly Twist with a twist-kick (round kick going against DOM) executed before landing.

name: Cali Roll
description: A Raiz with an extra 2 spins rotated before landing. First landed by Dan Pitlock.

name: Crashmoon
description: A Gainer Hook that lands in mega with a late/mega hook. Similar to a Shuriken Cutter but without the twist.

name: Flash Knife
description: A Flashkick that finishes with a hyperhook. Can be thought of as a pop moonkick.

name: Outstretched Corkscrew
description: A Corkscrew in an outstretched pose.

name: Raiz Hyperhook Turbo
description: A laid back Cheat 720 that finishes with an outside crescent kick and lands in the "turbo"/frontside stance.

name: Masterscoot Twist
description: A Masterscoot with an extra twist executed before landing.

name: Gainer Scissor Round
description: A Gainer Scissor that executes a round kick before landing.

name: Cheat 1080
description: A cheat kick which leaves the ground in (approximately) backside stance, completes (roughly) 720° in-air rotation, and finishes with an outside kick (hook or crescent) at the target.

name: Double Arabian
description: An Arabian with another frontflip before landing.

name: Valdez
description: A One-Handed Back Handspring, usually slightly off-axis.

name: Wrap Full Doubleleg
description: A Wrap Full with a doubleleg executed at the peak.

name: Full Hyperhook
description: A Full that finishes with a hyperhook. Could be considered a Backside 1080 with inversion.

name: Corkscrew Doubleleg
description: A Corkscrew that finishes with a Doubleleg.

name: Triple Full Hyperhook
description: A Triple Full that finishes with a hyperhook.

name: Wrap Full Round
description: A Wrap Full that executes a round kick before landing.

name: Tak Full Shuriken Hyperhook
description: A Tak Full that finishes with a shuriken hyperhook.

name: Flash Kick
description: The Flashkick is a backflip executed with a kick at the peak of the flip.

name: Dragonfly Moonkick
description: A Moonkick that initiates with a sidekick.

name: Aerial Mega
description: An Aerial that lands in mega, or the opposite leg with a slight extra rotation. Previously called hyper aerial.

name: Double Peter Pan Butterfly Twist
description: A Double Butterfly Twist with both hands at the hips.

name: X-Out-In Back-Out
description: A X-Out followed by a Back Tuck (two flips).

name: Full Twist
description: Traditionally a Backflip with a full rotation. However, the tricker-style full of the cartwheel-full is more off axis and under rotated rather than the tumbling-back full.

name: Skip Hook
description: The skip hook is an important, fundamental move to master. All vert kicks of higher rotation that end in hook or any hyperhook variations all have the same muscle-memory as a skip hook. How your skip hook looks will determine how all your other hook kicks will look like, so master it until it looks exactly how you want it to look.

name: Aerial Twist Gumbi Helicoptero
description: An Aerial Twist Gumbi that finishes with a helicoptero.

name: Backside 900 Hyper
description: The Backside 900 Hyper starts in Backside stance, leaves the ground off of both feet, rotates 540° in the air, then lands and finishes round kick and lands on that kicking foot in hyper stance.

name: Wrap Full
description: A Wrap Full is a Full Twist that takes off of one foot, where the other foot (left foot if left-spinner) is “wrapped” behind the other foot (right foot if left-spinner). Closely related to the Tak Full.

name: Double Full Snapu
description: A Double Full that finishes with a Snapu.

name: Double Full Doubleleg Double Twist
description: A Double Full Doubleleg with two extra twists executed before landing

name: Rodeo Corkscrew Snapu
description: A Corkscrew Snapu with a rodeo leg grab before the snapu.

name: Cheat 900 Hyper
description: A Cheat 900 that lands on the kicking (inside) leg in hyper.

name: Double Full Doubleleg
description: A Double Full that finishes with a Doubleleg.

name: Full Snapu-In Back-Out
description: A Full Snapu that finishes with another backflip, making this a double full-in, back-out variation.

name: One-Handed Cartwheel
description: A Cartwheel using the hand that’s closest to the ground.

name: Inward 360 Dive Roll
description: A "masterswing-ing" variation of the 360 Dive Roll.

name: Backside 1620
description: A vertical kick which initiates from backside stance, pops up, spins 3.5 times in the air, and round kicks at the end. Jordan Okubo first landed this trick on May 11, 2015.

name: Gainer Triple
description: A Gainer Flash with two switches, landing on the swing (inside) leg.

name: Gainer Scissor
description: A Gainer Arabian with a scissor (grabbing the inside kicking leg in a semi-piked position) executed at the peak of the flip.

name: Tak Double Full Hyper
description: A Tak Double Full that lands in hyper.

name: Rocketboi Scissor Switch
description: A Rocketboi with a scissor and another switch.

name: Straddle Corkscrew
description: A Corkscrew with a “straddle” position.

name: Corkscrew Kyro
description: A Boxcutter with an extra twist, landing back in complete stance.

name: Cheat 900 Double Knife
description: A Cheat 900 Double that finishes with a hyperhook.

name: Webster Half
description: A Webster with a half turn.

name: X-Out
description: A Back Tuck with a straddle / split-kick.

name: Cheat Feilong
description: A Tornado where the outside (pumped, non-kicking) leg kicks like a crescent, resulting in 2 kicks.

name: Wackknife Doubleleg
description: A Wackknife that finishes with a Doubleleg.

name: Full Doubleleg Double Twist
description: A Double Full Doubleleg with an extra rotation.

name: Gainer Tuck
description: A Back Tuck that takes off of one foot (swing), and usually travels forward (“gains” ground).

name: Gainer Switch Hawkeye
description: A Gainer Switch with a hawkeye (inside leg executing a hook kick against the DOM).

name: Full Up Hyperhook
description: An Iron Man Full that finishes with a hyperhook.

name: Full Cobra
description: A Full Twist that finishes with an arched position.

name: Back Pike
description: A Backflip with the “pike” position.

name: Rodeo Full Doubleleg
description: A Full Doubleleg with a rodeo leg grab.

name: Full Swipe
description: A Full Twist that finishes with a swipe (round kick that lands in hyper).

name: Full-In Full-Out
description: A Full with another full before landing - a double flipping, double twisting move.

name: Grand Master Rocketboi
description: A GMS with a Rocketboi executed before landing.

name: Roundoff
description: A Cartwheel that lands on two feet facing the way you came from.

name: Lonestar Hyperhook
description: A Lonestar that finishes with a hyperhook.

name: Lonestar Scissor
description: A Lonestar that finishes with a scissor.

name: Triple Corkscrew
description: A Corkscrew with three rotations. First landed by Scotty Skelton on May 25, 2009.

name: Sailor Moon Late Round
description: A Sailormoon that lands in a late/mega round.

name: Touchup Triple Butterfly Twist
description: A Triple Butterfly Twist where the inside hand touches the ground on takeoff.

name: Swing 1080
description: A vert kick that swings and leaves the ground in (roughly) backside, spins (roughly) 720° and executes an outside kick. Could be thought of as a vertical Boxcutter.

name: Swing 360
description: A turbo’d skip hook basically, or a Pop 360 from a swing.
A Tornado that lands in hyper (extra 180°) on the inside kicking leg.

name: Helicoptero E-Kick
description: A Cartwheel Helicoptero that finishes with an E-Kick.

name: Touchdown Corkscrew
description: A Corkscrew that finishes with a Touchdown Raiz, landing in Complete.

name: Kick Full Doubleleg
description: A Kick Full that finishes with a doubleleg.

name: Corkscrew Round
description: A Corkscrew that finishes with a round kick before landing. Could be thought of as an inverted Swing 900.

name: Gainer Arabian Grab Crowd Awakener
description: A Gainer Arabian with a grab that finishes with a Crowd Awakener.

name: Envergado Twist
description: An Envergado with an extra twist executed before landing. Can be thought of as an inverted Parafuso Gyro.

name: Cheat 1260 Double
description: A Cheat 1260 with 2 inside kicks.

name: Full Terada Grab
description: A Full that finishes with a Terada Grab.

name: Lotus Rodeo
description: A Lotus flip with a grab.

name: E-Kick
description: A Compasso (touchdown hook) with a switch executed before the hook.

name: Sailor Moon Doubleleg
description: A Sailor Moon that finishes with a Doubleleg.

name: Cheat 1080 Double
description: A Cheat 900 that lands in hyper and executes a jackknife before landing.

name: Arabian Unhalf-In Back-Out
description: An Arabian which unwinds back in the opposite direction + a backflip.

name: Grand Master Twist Doubleleg
description: A GMT that finishes with a doubleleg.

name: Takuraba Scissor
description: A Takuraba with a Scissor executed at the peak of the flip.

name: Pop Donut Boy Round
description: A Punch Donut Boy that finishes with a round kick.

name: Cartwheel Late Swipe
description: A Cartwheel that finishes with a late swipe.

name: Triple Full Round
description: A Triple Full with a round kick executed before landing. Could be thought of as an inverted Backside 1620.

name: Full Snapu Twist
description: A Full Snapu with an extra rotation executed before landing.

name: Full Scissor
description: A Full that finishes with a scissor, landing in mega.

name: Touchdown Wrap Full
description: A Wrap Full that finishes in a Touchdown Raiz.

name: Touchdown Full
description: A Full Twist that finishes with a Touchdown Raiz, landing in complete.

name: Corkscrew Doubleleg Twist
description: A Corkcrew Doubleleg that finishes with an extra twist – making this a double corkscrew variation.

name: Wrap Full Snapu
description: A Wrap Full with a Snapu executed at before landing, making this a Wrap Double Full variation.

name: Pop Feilong Knife
description: A Pop Feilong that finishes with a knife.

name: Pop 1080
description: The Pop 1080 starts in Frontside stance, leaves the ground off of both feet, rotates 900° in the air, then lands and finishes with a hook towards the target.

name: Touchdown Quat
description: A Gainer Arabian with an arm touching down before landing.

name: Dragonfly Corkscrew Round
description: A Dragonfly Corkscrew that finishes with a round kick.

name: Double Full-In Back-Out
description: A Double Full with a backflip before landing.

name: Rodeo Corkscrew Twist
description: A Rodeo Corkscrew with an extra twist.

name: Hurricane Kick
description: A Cheat 1080 with 3 outside kicks.

name: Wackknife
description: The Wackknife a cheat kick that has roughly 180° of in-air rotation, with 2-3 kicks (depending on how you count it). Basically a jackknife with no rotation.

name: Touchdown Butterfly Twist
description: A Butterfly Twist combined with a Touchdown Raiz. The hand should reach for the floor after the twist is initiated, and weight should be put on the hand similar to a Touchdown Raiz to give power for the next move.

name: Full Shuriken
description: A Full Twist with a shuriken executed before landing.

name: Full Tai Fighter Knife
description: A Full Tai Fighter that finishes with a hyperhook.

name: Sideswipe Late Swipe
description: A Sideswipe that finishes with a late swipe on the pseudo axis.

name: Butterfly Twist Round Late Round
description: A Butterfly Twist Round that rotates extra and executes another round kick.

name: Touchdown Raiz Roll
description: A shoulder roll that initiates from a Touchdown Raiz.

name: Lotus Shuriken
description: A Lotus Doubleleg that executes a shuriken (outside kick).

name: Doubleleg X-Out Hyperhook
description: A Doubleleg X-Out that finishes with a hyperhook.

name: Full Pike
description: A Full that finishes with a Front Pike.

name: Butterfly Twist Wackknife
description: A Butterfly Twist with a Wackknife executed before landing.

name: Cheat 900 Knife
description: A Cheat 900 Crowd Awakener that lands in a hyperhook.

name: Pop Tai Fighter
description: A Tai-Fighter is a Feilong with the round foot grabbed before the kick is released and is executed on the Doubleleg axis.

name: One-Elbow Cartwheel Twist
description: A One-Handed Cartwheel Twist but off of an elbow.

name: Grand Master Swipeknife
description: A GMS that finishes with a hyperhook.

name: Butterfly Twist Shuriken
description: A Butterfly Twist with an outside crescent kick (shuriken) executed before landing in complete stance.

name: Dragonfly Hyperhook
description: A Flash Knife with a sidekick for the first kick.

name: Full Round
description: A Full Twist with a round kick executed before landing.

name: Rodeo Grand Master Swipe
description: A GMS with a leg grab.

name: Full Feilong Late Swipeknife
description: A Full Feilong that finishes with a late swipe + hook kick.

name: Gainer Figure 4
description: A Gainer with a “figure-4” position.

name: Dragonfly Corkscrew Feilong Knife
description: A Dragonfly Corkscrew that finishes with a Feilong Knife (outside kick, inside kick, inside kick) for a total of 4 kicks.

name: Wrap Triple Full
description: A Wrap Full with two extra rotations.

name: Wrap Full Shuriken Hyperhook
description: A Wrap Full that finishes with a Shuriken + Hyperhook.

name: Backside 1260 Knife
description: A Backside 1260 that finishes with a jackknife.

name: Corkscrew Crowd Awakener Round
description: A Corkscrew Crowd Awakener with a round kick executed before landing.

name: Double Corkscrew Doubleleg
description: A Double Corkscrew that finishes with a doubleleg.

name: Cheat 720 Double
description: A Cheat 720 with two “kicks”, where the first kick is just a straightened chamber.

name: Cheat 720
description: A cheat vert kick that takes off in (roughly) backside stance, spins 360° and finishes with an outside (hook or crescent) at the target.

name: Triple Flash Kick Full
description: A Triple Flash Kick with a twist before landing.

name: Dragonfly Double Corkscrew Hyperhook
description: A Dragonfly Double Corkscrew that finishes with a hyperhook.

name: Double Corkscrew Shuriken
description: A Double Corkscrew that finishes with a shuriken (outside crescent) in complete stance.

name: Front Pike
description: A Frontflip that holds a “piked” position.

name: Dragonfly Corkscrew
description: A Corkscrew with a sidekick executed before the twist.

name: Backside 1440
description: The Backside 1440 starts in Backside stance, leaves the ground off of both feet, rotates 1080° in the air, then lands and finishes with a hook kick towards the target. Could be thought of as a vertical double full hyperhook.

name: Swing 900
description: A vert kick that swings and leaves the ground in (roughly) backside, spins (roughly) 540° and executes an inside kick. Could be thought of as a vertical Corkscrew Round.

name: Tak Full Wackknife
description: A Tak Full with a Wackknife executed before landing.

name: Triple Aerial Twist
description: An Aerial Twist with an extra two twists.

name: Envergado Double Twist
description: An Envergado with an extra two spins before landing.

name: Paraknife
description: A Parafuso that finishes with a hyperhook.

name: Double Corkscrew Doubleleg Twist
description: A Double Corkscrew Doubleleg that finishes with an extra twist, making this a Triple Corkscrew variation.

name: Parafuso Hawkeye
description: A Parafuso with a hawkeye executed after the doubleleg portion of the move. A hawkeye occurs when the inside (round-kicking) leg executes a hawkeye (hook kick going against the DOM).

name: Masterscoot
description: A Scoot with both hands with more emphasis on the masterswing. The Masterscoot also tends to be more inverted than the scoot, similar to a Cartwheel.

name: Wrap Full Late Round
description: A Wrap Full that finishes in mega stance with a late round kick.

name: Swing 900 Sidekick
description: A Swing 900 with a sidekick executed instead of a round kick.

name: Slice
description: A mix of a Back Pike with a Doubleleg.

name: Doubleleg
description: An outside flip that takes off of two feet and with piked legs and has varying degrees of rotation. Not to be confused with a piked sideflip – the hips never rise over the chest in a doubleleg.

name: Cheat 900
description: The Cheat 900 is a Cheat vert kick that leaves the ground in Backside stance, completes (approximately) 540° in-air rotation, finishing with a round kick towards the target.

name: Backside 720
description: The Backside 720 starts in Backside stance, rotates 180° in the air, then finishes with a hook kick. Could be thought of as a Skip Hook off of two feet.

name: Wackest Knife
description: A Wackknife with an extra hyperhook.

name: Backside 900 Sidekick
description: A Backside 900 that finishes with a sidekick instead of a round kick.

name: Sailor Moon Doubleleg Twist
description: A Sailor Moon Doubleleg with an extra twist executed before landing.

name: Full Wackknife Hyperhook
description: A Full Wackknife that finishes with a hyperhook.

name: Kick Full
description: A Flash Kick with an extra twist executed before landing.

name: Swipeknife Turbo
description: A Swipeknife that lands in hyper/turbo (frontside on both feet)

name: Wrap Full Swipe
description: A Wrap Full that finishes with a swipe, landing in hyper.

name: Triple Full Shuriken Hyperhook
description: A Triple Full that finishes with a shuriken hyperhook.

name: Jackknife Shuriken
description: A Jackknife that lands on the outside leg with a shuriken-style kick.

name: Pop Swipeknife
description: A Swipeknife that takes off in frontside pop.

name: Sideswipe Late Round
description: A Sideswipe that lands in mega and executes another round before landing.

name: Arabian Scissor Round
description: A Full Round with a scissor grab in the middle.

name: Cheat 900 Sidekick
description: A Cheat 900 with a sidekick rather than a round kick.

name: Cheat 900 Crowd Awakener Knife
description: A Cheat 900 Crowd Awakener that lands in a hyperhook.

name: Full Rocketboi
description: A Full that finishes with a Rocketboi.

name: Full Shurikane
description: A Shurikane from full.

name: Janitor Scissor Twist
description: A Janitor Twist with a scissor executed before the twist is initiated.

name: Sideswipe
description: An inverted 540 kick, or a Raiz with a swipe.

name: Arabian
description: An Arabian starts out with a backflip into a half twist that begins immediately after takeoff, and then continues into a front flip.

name: X-Out Full
description: An X-Out with an extra twist.

name: Double Full Crowd Awakener
description: A Double Full that finishes with a Crowd Awakener / split kick.

name: Full Snapu Hyperhook
description: A Full Snapu that finishes with a hyperhook.

name: Corkscrew Skullsnapper
description: A Tucked Corkscrew with an extra twist.

name: Wrap Arabian
description: A Cart Arabian that takes off from a wrap-transition or a Takuraba from wrap takeoff.

name: Scoot Hyper
description: A Scoot that lands in hyper.

name: Cheat 900 Paraknife
description: A Cheat 900 Parafuso that finishes with a knife.

name: Rodeo Boxcutter
description: A Boxcutter with a rodeo leg grab.

name: Full Doubleleg
description: A Full Twist with a Doubleleg executed before landing.

name: Wrap Full Pike
description: A Wrap Full with a Pike - similar to a Wrap Full Doubleleg but flipping on a slightly different axis.

name: Doubleleg Twist
description: A Doubleleg with an extra twist executed, landing the trick in complete.

name: Webster Axe
description: A Webster with an axe kick / step-out.

name: Flash Helicoptero
description: A Flashkick that finishes with a Helicoptero.

name: Handcuff Corkscrew
description: A Corkscrew with a “handcuff” hand position.

name: Cheat 900 Doubleleg
description: A Cheat 900 that finishes with a parafuso/doubleleg instead of a round kick.

name: Full Doubleleg Hyperhook
description: A Full Doubleleg that finishes with a hyperhook.

name: Rodeo Backflip Full Down
description: A Rodeo Backflip with a twist before landing.

name: Corkscrew Snapu Hyper
description: A Corkscrew Snapu that lands in hyper stance.

name: Sailor Gumbi
description: A Sailor Moon where the planted hand does not leave the ground. Can be thought of as a Gumbi with the right hand (assuming spinning to the left) instead of both.

name: Butterfly Kick Late Hook
description: A Butterfly-Kick that lands in semi (landing position) with a hook executed at the end.

name: Cheat 900 Double
description: A Cheat 900 with two inside kicks. Like a 540 late Round.

name: Double Corkscrew
description: A Corkscrew with two rotations. Could be thought of as a double full off of one foot.

name: Sailor Moon Reversao
description: A Sailor Moon with a Reversao.

name: Aerial Scissor
description: An Aerial with a scissor executed at the peak of the flip.

name: One-Handed Cartwheel Twist
description: A One-Handed Cartwheel with an extra twist, landing in complete.

name: Arabian Scissor Half
description: An Arabian Scissor with an extra half turn - making this a full variation.

name: Frappe
description: A Full Late Round that swipes / pseudo-flips into hyper stance.

name: Masterswipe Helicoptero
description: A Masterswipe that executes a Helicoptero before landing.

name: Rodeo Full Wackknife
description: A Full Wackknife with a rodeo grab.

name: Wrap Double Full
description: A Wrap Full with an extra rotation.

name: Tak Double Full
description: A Tak Full with an extra rotation.

name: Full-In Back-Out Hyper
description: A Full-In Back-Out that lands in hyper. Could be thought of as an "on-axis" Frappe.

name: Broken Full
description: A Full Twist that finishes like a Broken Touchdown Raiz.

name: Butterfly Twist Hyper
description: A Butterfly Twist that lands in hyper.

name: Butterfly Twist Knife
description: A Butterfly Twist that finishes with a knife (round kick + hook kick)

name: Superman Front
description: A Frontflip that hits a “Superman” pose at the peak of the flip.

name: Pop 900
description: The Pop 900 starts in Frontside stance, leaves the ground off of both feet, rotates 720° in the air, then lands and finishes with a round kick towards the target.

name: Lotus Crowd Awakener
description: A Lotus Flip with a split kick.

name: Full Up
description: A Full Twist that stalls on the way up (usually in the "Ironman" hand position).

name: Kick Full Snapu
description: A Kick Full that finishes with a snapu.

name: Dragonfly Double Corkscrew
description: A Double Corkscrew that initiates with a dragonfly / sidekick.

name: Full Late Round
description: A Full that finishes with a mega round / late round.

name: Sideflip Round
description: A sideflip with a round kick executed before landing.

name: Raiz-In
description: A Raiz with an extra “backflip” executed before landing. Note: The execution of this move is more like a raiz-in-shant-out.

name: Touchdown Aerial Twist
description: An Aerial Twist combined with a Touchdown Raiz.

name: Illusion Twist
description: Basically a Pop 360 from a Butterfly-Kick setup. A lot of people see this as a Butterfly Twist variation, but there is actually no twist happening, hence the name “illusion”.

name: Lotus Late Round
description: A Lotus Doubleleg that lands in mega and executes round kick.

name: Full Wackknife Round
description: A Full Wackknife that finishes with a round kick.

name: Double Full McDirty
description: A Double Full that finishes with a Feilong Snapu (aka McDirty), making this a triple full variation.

name: Triple Full Hyper
description: A Triple Full that lands in hyper stance.

name: Blasterscoot
description: An inverted roundkick with a handplant (opposite hand of kicking leg). A whole 360° is done on the floor.

name: Full Snapu Swipe
description: A Full Snapu that finishes with a swipe.

name: Shurikane
description: A Shuriken Cutter that finishes with another hyperhook. Or a Sheep Shearer with 3 outside kicks.

name: Triple Corkscrew Round
description: A Triple Corkscrew that finishes with a round kick.

name: Gainer Arabian
description: An Arabian from a swing/gainer takeoff.

name: Full Snapu Hyper
description: A Full Snapu that lands in hyper.

name: Full Feilong
description: A Full Twist with a Feilong (outside kick + inside kick).

name: Gainer Scissor Twist
description: A Gainer Scissor with with an extra rotation that finishes in complete - making this a double corkscrew variation. Similar to a Corkscrew Snapu but with the kick occuring earlier.

name: Jackknife
description: A Cheat 720 with a round kick executed before the hook kick or a 540 that finishes with a hook kick. Could be thought of as a Narabong all executed in the air.

name: Touchup Double Butterfly Twist
description: A Double Butterfly Twist where the inside hand touches the ground on takeoff.

name: Front X-Out
description: A Frontflip with a split kick / straddle.

name: Gainer Flash
description: The Gainer Flash (often referred to just as “gainer”) is the fundamental trick on which all backswing tricks are built upon. It flips on almost a completely inverted axis, but a bit of leeway is allowed.

name: Raiz Shurikane
description: A laid back Hurricane kick.

name: Butterfly Twist Double Round
description: A Butterfly Twist with two round kicks executed before landing.

name: Tak Triple Full
description: A Tak Full with an extra two rotations.

name: Full Feilong Knife
description: A Full Feilong that finishes with a hyperhook.

name: Full Cobra Twist
description: A Full Cobra with another rotation executed before landing – making this a double full variation.

name: Butterfly Twist Swipe
description: A Butterfly Twist Round that kicks all the way through into hyper.

name: Cartwheel Twist
description: A Cartwheel with an extra twist, landing in complete.

name: Butterfly Twist Feilong Swipe
description: A Butterfly Twist Feilong that finishes with a swipe.

name: Corkscrew Crowd Awakener Hyper
description: A Corkscrew Crowd Awakener that lands in hyper.

name: Backside 1080 Shuriken
description: A Backside 1080 with an outside crescent kick that lands on the kicking foot, landing in complete stance.

name: Cheat 900 Doubleleg Twist
description: A Cheat 900 Doubleleg with an extra twist, landing back in complete stance.

name: Double Butterfly Twist
description: A Butterfly Twist with another spin executed before landing.

name: Cheat 720 Turbo
description: A Cheat 720 that lands on both legs (turbo) with an outside crescent kick.

name: Palmkick Kyro
description: A Palmkick with a half twist, landing in complete.

name: Sailor Moon Snapu
description: A Sailor Moon with a Snapu executed before landing.

name: Butterfly Twist Hyperhook
description: A Butterfly Twist that finishes with a hyperhook.

name: Crowd Awakener Knife
description: A Crowd Awakener that finishes with a hyperhook.

name: Backside 1260 Feilong
description: The Backside 1260 starts in Backside stance, leaves the ground off of both feet, rotates 900° in the air, then lands and finishes with an outside kick and an inside kick at its target.

name: Dragonfly Triple Corkscrew
description: A Triple Corkscrew that initiates with a dragonfly / sidekick.

name: Tak Double Full Round
description: A Tak Double Full with a round kick executed before landing. Could be thought of as a laid-back Cheat 1260.

name: Sailor Moon Round
description: A Sailor Moon with a round kick executed before landing.

name: Double Sideflip
description: A sideflip with two flips.

name: Rodeo Gainer Switch
description: A Gainer Switch with a leg grab.

name: Butterfly Twist Doubleleg
description: A Butterfly Twist with a Doubleleg executed before landing.

name: Tornado Sidekick
description: A Tornado with a sidekick instead of a round kick.

name: Double Full Round
description: A Double Full with a round kick executed before landing. Could be thought of as a Backside 1260 with some inversion.

name: Dive Roll
description: The Dive Roll is a crucial pre-requisite to all forward flipping techniques, and a good skill to have for bailing safety.

name: Butterfly Kick Scissor
description: A Butterfly Kick with a scissor.

name: Sketchdown Raiz
description: A Masterswing Valdez that looks similar to the Touchdown Raiz

name: Double Back Tuck
description: A Back Tuck with two rotations.

name: Double Full Hyperhook
description: A Double Full that finishes with a hyperhook. Could be thought of as an inverted Backside 1440.

name: Pop 720 Double
description: A Pop 720 with two outside kicks. Can be thought of as a Pop 360 that rotates extra and finishes in a hyperhook.

name: Butterfly Twist Shurikane
description: A Butterfly Twist combined with a Shurikane.

name: Swipeknife
description: An inverted Jackknife, or a Sideswipe that finishes with a hyperhook.

name: Doubleleg Twist Round
description: A Doubleleg Twist that executes a round kick before landing.

name: 360 Cartwheel Twist
description: A 360 Cartwheel with another twist executed before landing.

name: Sideflip
description: A tucked flip that goes side to side.

name: Gainer Figure 4 Sidekick
description: A Gainer Figure-4 with a sidekick. Not totally flipped, but more on the Flick Flack axis.

name: Full Swipeknife
description: A Full that finishes with a Swipeknife.

name: Aerial Twist Doubleleg
description: An Aerial Twist that finishes with a Doubleleg.

name: Corkscrew Feilong Knife
description: A Corkscrew Feilong that finishes with a hyperhook.

name: Double Butterfly Twist Snapu
description: A Double Butterfly Twist that finishes with a Snapu, making this a Triple Butterfly Twist variation.

name: Backside 900 Gyro
description: A Backside 900 Gyro is a Backside 900 with a an extra 360° executed before landing. Can be thought of as a vertical Full Snapu.

name: Sailor Moon Twist
description: Sailor Moon with an extra twist executed before landing.

name: Macaron
description: A tucked Aerial that with another pseudo-flip that lands with a hyperhook.

name: Filipino
description: A Full with 1.5 twist and finishes with a front flip. Could be thought of as an Arabian with an extra spin before flipping.

name: Back Tuck
description: The Back Tuck (DOUBLEbed “back flip” by most) is the most fundamental and crucial move that a tricker can learn. Mastery of the backflip is an important fundamental building block – it teach air awareness and builds comfort-ability with flipping upside down.

name: Double Butterfly Twist Round
description: A Double Buterfly Twist with a round kick executed before landing.

name: Cheat 900 Gyro
description: A Cheat 900 with an extra rotation, landing back in complete stance.

name: Grand Master Scoot
description: A Masterscoot with no hands. Could be thought of as a darkside gainer switch.

name: Pop 360 Gyro Doubleleg
description: A Pop 360 Gyro where a Doubleleg is executed before landing, thus adding an extra 180° to the original move.

name: Double Corkscrew Snapu
description: A Double Corkscrew that finishes with a snapu, making this a triple corkscrew variation.

name: Scoot Twist
description: A Scoot with an extra twist executed before landing

name: Cheat 720 Twist
description: A Raiz with an extra twist. There is some debate whether “raiz twist” and “cheat 7 twist” are the same thing, but if they differ, they differ in shape and timing, but the axis is relatively the same. Originally created by “cheating” a Double Butterly Twist. Despite its name, this move has no relation to the Cheat 720 kick.

name: Twist Knife
description: A Jackknife with a Twist-Kick (round kicking going against DOM) instead of a round kick.

name: Shuriken Cutter Scissor
description: A Corkscrew Shuriken Cutter that finishes with a scissor, landing in mega stance.

name: Double Corkscrew Shuriken Cutter
description: A Double Corkscrew that finishes with a shuriken hyperhook.

name: Corkscrew Swipeknife
description: A Corkscrew that finishes with a Swipeknife.

name: Touchdown Swipe
description: A Touchdown Raiz that swipes and lands on the opposite leg.

name: Reversao
description: The Reversao is similar to a front walkover, but on the raiz axis. Originates from Capoeira.

name: Corkscrew Shuriken
description: A Corkscrew with a Shuriken (outside crescent kick landing in complete stance).

name: Terada Grab In Shant Out
description: A Terada Grab with an extra pseudo flip / shant.

name: Rodeo Full Hyperhook
description: A Full Hyperhook with a rodeo leg grab.

name: Full Tai-Fighter Hyperhook
description: A Full Hyperhook with a Tai-Fighter leg grab.

name: Corkscrew Sidewinder
description: A Corkscrew that finishes with a Sidewinder, making this a double corkscrew variation.

name: Pop 360 Shuriken
description: The Pop 360 Hyper starts in Frontside stance, leaves the ground off of both feet, rotates 180° in the air, then lands and finishes with an outside cresecent kick towards the target and lands in complete stance. This move is often the first Shuriken that trickers learn, and is vitally important for future shuriken variations.

name: Machine
description: A Spyder with hands.

name: Front Handspring
description: A forward flipping tumbling skill which uses your hands to propel and flip you over.

name: 540 Gyroknife
description: A 540 Gyro that finishes with a hyperhook. Could be thought of as a vertical Snapu Hyperhook.

name: Rodeo Snapu
description: A Snapu with a leg grab.

name: Back Tuck
description: The Back Tuck (dubbed “back flip” by most) is the most fundamental and crucial move that a tricker can learn. Mastery of the backflip is an important fundamental building block – it teach air awareness and builds comfort-ability with flipping upside down.

name: Full Swipe Late Round
description: A Full Swipe that finishes with a late round.

name: Double Corkscrew Round
description: A Double Corkscrew that finishes with a round kick.

name: Snapu
description: A sideswipe with an extra twist before landing. Invented by Steve Terada.

name: Doubleleg Rodeo
description: A Doubleleg variation that initiates exactly like the base move, but then flips backwards with the same aesthetic of a Rodeo Backflip.

name: Snapu Hyperhook
description: A Snapu that lands in a hyperhook. Can be thought of as a laid back / inverted 540 Gyroknife.

name: Gainer Switch Hyperhook
description: A Gainer Switch that finishes with a hyperhook.

name: Corkscrew Crowd Awakener
description: A Corkscrew with a split kick / straddle.

name: Cheat 1260
description: The Cheat 1260 is a Cheat vert kick that leaves the ground in (approximately) Backside stance, completes (roughly) 1080° in-air rotation, finishing with a round kick towards the target.

name: Lonestar Twist
description: A Lonestar with an extra half rotation, finishing in complete.

name: Kick Double Full
description: A Flash Kick with two rotations executed before landing.

name: Dragonfly Corkscrew Doubleleg
description: A Dragonfly Corkscrew that finishes with a Doubleleg.

name: Corkscrew Feilong
description: A Corkscrew that finishes with a Feilong (outside kick followed by an inside kick).

name: Full Snapu Round
description: A Full Snapu that finishes with a round kick before landing.

name: Dragonfly Corkscrew Sidewinder Late Round
description: A Dragonfly Corkscrew / Gainer Sidewinder that finishes with a late round.

name: Boxcutter Turbo
description: A Boxcutter that lands on both feet in frontside.

name: Butterfly Twist Hawkeye
description: A Butterfly Twist that executes a hawkeye (inside leg executing a hook kick against the DOM)

name: Corkscrew Doubleleg Late Round
description: A Corkscrew Doubleleg that at finishes with a late round.

name: Rodeo Full
description: A Full Twist with a leg grab

name: Back Handspring
description: The Back Handspring is a gymnastics, tumbling move that takes off of two feet, jumps backward onto the hands and lands on both feet. Used to gain and build momentum for bigger tricks.

name: Touchdown Raiz Twist
description: A Touchdown Raiz with an extra twist, landing in complete.

name: Raiz Hyperhook
description: A Raiz that finishes with a hyperhook. Could be thought of as an inverted Cheat 720.

name: Tornado
description: The Tornado is the most basic cheat kick and one of the first moves a tricker will learn. It forms the basis of all cheat kicks after.

name: Touchdown Raiz
description: The Touchdown Raiz is part of the Raiz family of tricks. It utilizes the opposite hand that touches the ground as the Sailor Moon. It is also one of the most popular of set-ups for trickers.

name: Gainer Scissor Late Round
description: A Gainer Scissor that rotates extra into a late round.

name: Crackknife
description: A Wackknife on the Raiz axis.

name: Doubleleg Double Twist
description: A Doubleleg with two extra spins executed before landing.

name: Butterfly Twist Snapu
description: A Butterfly Twist with a Snapu executed before landing. This completes two full rotations, therefore making it a Double Butterfly Twist variation.

name: Sidewinder
description: A Butterfly Kick where the outside leg initiates an extra twist while in an outstretched, arched position.

name: Full Feilong Double
description: A Full Feilong with an extra kick, landing in mega stance.

name: Full Up Rocketboi Twist
description: An Ironman Full Rocketboi with an extra twist.

name: Tak Full Round
description: A Tak Full that finishes with a round. Can be thought of as a Cheat 900 with more inversion.

name: Gainer-In Shant-Out
description: An off-axis double flip that initiates from a gainer. Could be thought of as a more off-axis double gainer.

name: Full Crowd Awakener
description: A Full Twist with a Crowd Awakener / Straddle before landing.

name: Peter Pan Double Corkscrew
description: A Double Corkscrew with both hands at the hip.

name: Pop Tornado
description: The most basic of pop kicks. The Pop Tornado starts in Frontside stance, leaves the ground off of both feet, rotates 180° in the air, then lands and finishes with a round kick towards the target.

name: Front Half
description: A Front Flip with a half turn.

name: Cheat 720 Twist Broken
description: A Cheat 720 Twist that finishes with a broken. Usually lands in hyper or semi stance.

name: Webster X-Out
description: A Webster with an x-out / straddle.

name: Pop Feilong
description: The Pop Feilong starts off like a Pop 360 and finishes with an inside kick.

name: Rodeo Janitor Twist
description: A Janitor Twist with a rodeo grab before the twist.

name: Double Full
description: A Full Twist with an extra rotation before landing.

name: Rocketboi Scissor Snapu
description: A rocketboi scissor with a snapu executed before landing, making this a double full variation.

name: Rocketboi Full Doubleleg Rocketboi
description: Has the visuals of a rocketboi on the way up and a rocketboi on the way down.

name: Double Nike
description: An off-axis double backflip with body in a position resembling the Nike logo.

name: 540 Gyro
description: A 540 with an extra twist, landing back in Complete stance.

name: Backside 1080
description: The Backside 1080 starts in Backside stance, leaves the ground off of both feet, rotates 720° in the air, then lands and finishes with a hook kick towards the target.

name: Pop 360
description: The Pop 360 starts in Frontside stance, leaves the ground off of both feet, rotates 180° in the air, then lands and finishes with an outside crescent kick towards the target and lands in turbo (both feet). This trick is also a hyper, because Pop 180 Hook (TKT) is not often used in tricking. This trick is vitally important for Illusion Twist and other similar tricks that end in turbo.

name: Spyder
description: The Spyder initiates very similar to how a Raiz would, but instead of flipping over the top, the Spyder flatspins around very similar to a Butterfly Kick.

name: Double Full Snapu Twist
description: A Double Full Snapu with an extra twist executed before landing.

name: Helicoptero
description: A Cartwheel with a leg circle, originating from the martial art, Capoeira. Landing in mega stance.

name: Takuraba
description: A Frontflip that initiates from a cheat setup. Could be considered a Wrap Front from cheat setup.

name: Front Axe
description: A Frontflip that finishes with a step-out / axe kick.

name: Pop 900 Hyper
description: The Pop 900 Hyper starts in Frontside stance, leaves the ground off of both feet, rotates 720° in the air, then lands and finishes with a hyper’d round kick towards the target and lands on that kicking foot.

name: Sailor Moon Wackknife
description: A Sailor Moon that is combined with a Wackknife.

name: Butterfly Kick Helicoptero Round
description: A Butterfly Kick Helicoptero with an extra round kick.

name: Swing 1260
description: A vert kick that swings and leaves the ground in (roughly) backside, spins (roughly) 900° and executes an inside kick. Could be thought of as a vertical Double Corkscrew Round.

name: Arabian Half
description: An Arabian with a half turn, making this a full variation.

name: Double Full Swipe
description: A Double Full that finishes with a Swipe. Could be considered an inverted Backside 1260 Hyper.

name: Doubleleg Sidekick
description: A Doubleleg that finishes with a sidekick.

name: Snapu Doubleleg
description: A Snapu with a doubleleg executed at the end.

name: Cheat 900 Double Tai Fighter
description: A Cheat 900 with a leg grab in between both kicks.

name: Arabian Pike Snapu
description: An Arabian Pike that finishes with a snapu, making this a double full variation.

name: Sailor Moon Hawkeye
description: A Sailor Moon that finishes with a hawkeye (hook kick executed with the round leg).

name: Double Doubleleg
description: A Doubleleg with two flips. First landed by Zen Kajihara on June 5, 2020.

name: Arabian Scissor
description: An Arabian with a scissor executed before landing.

name: Grand Master Swipe
description: A Masterswipe with no hands – could be thought of as an aerial that takes off of the “wrong” leg.

name: Pop 360 Gyro
description: A Pop 360 with an extra 360° spin (aka gyro/kyro)before landing, landing back in Frontside.

name: Parafuso Twist-Kick
description: A Parafuso with a Twist-Kick (round kicking going against DOM).

name: Backside 1260 Wackknife
description: A Backside 1260 that finishes with a wackknife.

name: Backside 900 Feilong
description: A Backside 900 that finishes with a Feilong.

name: Full Snapu Snapu
description: A Full Snapu with another Snapu executed before landing.

name: Envergado
description: A Raiz that executes a Doubleleg at the peak of the jump and lands on both feet.

name: Butterfly Twist-In
description: A Butterfly Twist with an extra “backflip” executed before landing.

name: Backside 900
description: The Backside 900 starts in Backside stance, leaves the ground off of both feet, rotates 540° in the air, then lands and finishes with a round kick towards the target. The Backside 900 is very important for learning similar tricks like the Cheat 900 and the Swing 900, as they have the same amount of rotation, but different take off.

name: Front Tuck
description: A forward flipping trick with a tuck – the most “basic” form of the front flip.

name: Full Hyperhook Turbo
description: A Full Hyperhook that finishes in turbo (on both feet in frontside).

name: Tak Full
description: The Tak Full is a cheat setup into a Wrap Full. Tak Fulls from a cheat takeoff rarely reach a high degree of inversion, and tend to be closer to the horizontal plane.

name: Backside 900 Knife
description: A Backside 900 Knife is a Backside 900 with a Jackknife executed, making it a Backside 1080 variation. Can be thought of as a vertical, non-flipped Full Swipeknife.

name: Cheat 1080 Shuriken
description: A Cheat 1080 that finishes with a shuriken instead of a hook. This has the same rotational value as a Cheat 1260.

name: Lotus Doubleleg Hyperhook
description: A Lotus Doubleleg that lands in a hyperhook.

name: Janitor Twist
description: A Janitor Flip with an extra spin before landing. Can be considered a “punched” butterfly twist.

name: Triple Full
description: A Full Twist with an extra two rotations.

name: Arabian Axe
description: An Arabian that finishes with an axe kick / step-out.

name: Touchdown Tak Full
description: A Tak Full that finishes like a touchdown raiz.

name: Full Down
description: A Back Tuck with a late twist, making this a full variation.

name: Double Full Doubleleg Twist
description: A Full Doubleleg Twist with an extra rotation before landing.

name: Quad Corkscrew
description: A Corkscrew with four rotations. First landed by Michael Guthrie on January 11, 2016.

name: Rodeo Full Round
description: A Full Round with a rodeo grab.

name: Corkscrew McDirty
description: A Corkscrew Feilong that finishes with a twist.

name: Grand Master Scissor
description: A GMS that finishes with a scissor.

name: Cheat 1440
description: The Cheat 1440 is a Cheat vert kick that leaves the ground in (approximately) Backside stance, completes (roughly) 1080° in-air rotation, finishing with an outside kick towards the target.

name: Cheat 900 Rodeo
description: A Cheat 900 with a leg grab.

name: Butterfly Twist Shuriken Hyperhook
description: A Butterfly Twist Shuriken / Illusion Twist that finishes with a hyperhook.

name: Tak Full Swipe
description: A Tak Full that finishes with a swipe, landing in hyper.

name: Corkscrew Swipe
description: A Corkscrew that finishes with a swipe (round kick that lands in hyper).

name: Full Up Crowd Awakener
description: An Ironman Full that finishes with a crowd awakener / split kick.

name: Gainer Scissor Swipe
description: A Gainer Scissor that lands in hyper on the kicking leg.

name: Sailor Moon Hyperhook
description: A Sailor Moon that finishes with a hyperhook.

name: Gainer Rocketboi
description: A Gainer with a Rocketboi executed at the peak of the flip.

name: Corkscrew Shuriken Kyro
description: A Cork Shuiken Cutter with an extra half turn landing on both feet in backside.

name: Butterfly Twist
description: A Butterfly Kick with an extra 360° rotation done in the air before landing on the horizontal axis.

name: Corkscrew Swipe Late Round
description: A Corkscrew Swipe that finishes with a late / mega round.

name: Terada Full
description: A Terada Grab with an extra twist, landing in complete.

name: Full Doubleleg Hawkeye
description: A Full Doubleleg that finishes with a hawkeye (inside leg executing a hook kick against the DOM).

name: Back-In X-Out
description: A Back Tuck followed by a Rocketboi (two flips).

name: Back-In Rocketboi-Out
description: A Back Tuck followed by a Rocketboi (two flips).

name: Parafuso Gyro
description: A Parafuso with an extra twist, landing back in Complete. Could be thought of as a vertical Envergado Twist.

name: Corkscrew Swipe Late Swipe
description: A Corkscrew Swipe that finishes with a late swipe on the pseudo-flip axis.

name: Palmkick
description: Can be thought of as a Cartwheel while only planting the hand that’s farthest from the floor and hook kicking. Like a “grounded” Skip Hook.

name: Gainer X-Out
description: A Gainer with an X-Out / straddle.

name: Wrap Double Full Snapu
description: A Wrap Double Full that finishes with a Snapu, making this a Wrap Triple Full variation.

name: Cheat 900 Feilong
description: A Cheat 900 with a Feilong executed before landing.

name: Palmkick Scissor Swipe
description: A Palmkick Kyro with a scissor and then landing on the kicking leg.

name: Broken Scrubba
description: A Scrubba with another hand-plant switch that lands in hyper, creating the “broken” visual.

name: Lotus Doubleleg
description: The Lotus is a swingthrough that doesn’t quite swing backwards, but is similar to to masterswing, but with the inside kicking leg and flips on the Raiz/Vert axis. The lotus swing/axis is very similar a tunnel flip.

name: Cheat 1620
description: The Cheat 1620 is a Cheat vert kick that leaves the ground in (approximately) Backside stance, completes (roughly) 1260° in-air rotation, finishing with an inside kick towards the target.

name: Full Up Doubleleg
description: An Ironman Full / Full Up with a Doubleleg executed before landing.

name: Full Doubleleg Twist Doubleleg
description: A Full Doubleleg Twist that finishes with a Doubleleg.

name: Raiz Reversao
description: A Raiz with a reversao (or scissor) executed at the peak.

name: Cheat 900 Double Hyper
description: A Cheat 900 Double that lands on the inside leg in hyper.

name: Cartwheel
description: While the “gymnastics cartwheel” has a 180° stance change from start to finish, the “tricker cartwheel” goes completely side-to-side. Trickers tend to use the side-to-side cartwheel because of how the cartwheel sets for side-fulls, wraps, and masterswings.

name: Pop Donut Boy
description: A Full Pike with no inversion. The original Donut Boy comes from a swing setup.

name: Double Full Shurikane
description: A Double Full Shuriken Hyperhook that finishes with another late hook.

name: Popcorn Hyper
description: The Popcorn that lands in hyper stance.

name: Donut Boy Hyperhook
description: A Donut Boy that finishes with a hyperhook.

name: Shurikane Late Hook
description: A Shurikane with an extra rotation and a late hook kick.

name: Dragonfly Shuriken Cutter
description: A Dragonfly Corkscrew that finishes with a Shuriken Hyperhook.

name: Jackknife Turbo
description: A Jackknife that lands back in frontside on both feet like an Illusion Twist. This landing is known as “hyper” in TKT and “turbo” in mainstream.

name: Full Shuriken Hyperhook
description: A Full Shuriken that finishes with a hyperhook.

name: Full Crowd Awakener Snapu
description: A Full Crowd Awakener with an extra twist before landing.

name: Full-In Back-Out
description: A Full with another backflip before landing.

name: Snatch Cannon
description: A Corkscrew with an extra flip. First landed by Tim Farley on February 25, 2014.

name: Tak Double Full Hyperhook
description: A Tak Double Full that finishes with a hyperhook. Could be thought of as a Cheat 1440 on the Tak axis.

name: Rodeo Full Shuriken
description: A Full Shuriken with a rodeo leg grab.

name: Quad Full
description: A backflip with four rotations executed before landing.

name: Spyder Twist Round
description: A Spyder Twist that executes a round kick before landing.

name: Tornado Hawkeye
description: A Tornado with a hawkeye (inside leg executing a hook kick against the DOM)

name: Backside 1260 Feilong Knife
description: A Backside 1260 Feilong that finishes with a hyperhook.

name: Scrubba
description: A Gumbi where the hands are placed down at separate times.

name: Full Kyro
description: A Full Hyperhook with an extra half rotation, landing in complete stance.

name: Dragonfly Double Corkscrew Round
description: A Dragonfly Double Corkscrew with a round kick executed before landing.

name: Janitor Flip
description: A Spyder that takes off of two-feet. Or a front half / Barahni that happens on the flat-spin axis.

name: Webster
description: A Front Flip off of one foot, taking off with a swing through.

name: Gainer Late Round
description: A Gainer that finishes with a late round.

name: Shuriken Cutter
description: A Corkscrew Shuriken that finishes with a hyperhook.

name: Outstretched Boxcutter
description: A Boxcutter with outstretched arms.

name: Corkscrew
description: A Gainer Flash with an extra rotation before landing – or a Back Full off of one leg.

name: Corkscrew Crowd Awakener Knife
description: A Corkscrew Crowd Awakener that finishes with a hyperhook.

name: Pop 1440
description: The Pop 1440 starts in Frontside stance, leaves the ground off of both feet, rotates 1080° in the air, then lands and finishes with a round kick towards the target.

name: Butter Knife
description: A Butterfly Kick that finishes with a hook kick while maintaining the flat-spin axis.

name: Full Snapu Doubleleg
description: A Full Snapu that finishes with a Doubleleg.

name: Full Up Twist
description: A Full-Up with an extra twist on the way down.

name: Pop 720
description: The Pop 720 starts in Frontside stance, leaves the ground off of both feet, rotates 540° in the air, then lands and finishes with a hook kick towards the target.

name: Wrap Full Hyperhook
description: A Wrap Full that finishes with a hyperhook.

name: Gainer Wackknife
description: A Gainer with a Wackknife executed at the peak of the flip.

name: Full Elbow Gumbi
description: A Full Gumbi that uses elbows rather than hands.

name: Jackknife 1080
description: A Cheat 1080 that starts with a Jackknife.

name: Butterfly Twist Shuriken Twist
description: A Butterfly Twist Shuriken with an extra spin that makes the trick finish in complete.

name: Grand Master Twist
description: A GMS with with an extra rotation, landing in complete stance. Very similar to a Kroc (reversed corkscrew).

name: Snapu Twist
description: A sideswipe with two extra twists before landing. First landed by Michael Guthrie.

name: Full Snapu
description: A Full with a snapu executed before landing – making this a double full variation.

name: Rocketboi
description: A Backflip Pike with one hand reaching across the legs and the other hand reaching behind.

name: Tak Full Pizzaboy
description: A Tak Full Swipe + Scissor (aka Pizzaboy).

name: Full Wackknife
description: A Full that finishes with a Wackknife.

name: Rodeo Full Snapu
description: A Full Snapu with a rodeo leg grab before the snapu.

name: Butterfly Kick Helicoptero
description: A Butterfly Kick with a Helicoptero executed mid-way through the trick.

name: Snapu Round
description: A Snapu with a round kick executed at the end.

name: Butterfly Twist Axe
description: A Butterfly Twist with an axe kick executed before landing.

name: Cheat 900 Crowd Awakener
description: A Cheat 900 with a Crowd Awakener / straddle / split kick executed before landing.

name: Tak Full Kyro
description: A Tak Full Hyperhook with an extra half rotation, making this a Tak Double Full variation.

name: Pop Snapu
description: A Pop Swipe with an extra twist. Or a Snapu that initiates from a frontside pop rather than a cheat setup.

name: Shattermoon
description: A Crashmoon with another late hook.

name: Double Corkscrew Wackknife
description: A Double Corkscrew that finishes with a wackknife.

name: Backside 1260
description: The Backside 1260 starts in Backside stance, leaves the ground off of both feet, rotates 900° in the air, then lands and finishes with a round kick towards the target.

name: Russian Front
description: A Front Tuck where the arms set behind, rather than in front.

name: Full Doubleleg Twist
description: A Full Doubleleg with an extra twist executed before landing.

name: Pop 360 Gyro Round
description: A Pop 360 Gyro where a round kick is executed before landing, thus adding an extra 180° to the original move. The Pop 360 Gyro Round has the same amount of rotation as a Pop 900.

name: Wrap Arabian Scissor
description: A Wrap Arabian with a scissor / step-out.

name: Lonestar
description: An Arabian with a Pike that flips over the side.

name: Arabian Scissor Hyperhook
description: An Arabian Scissor that finishes with a hyperhook.

name: Wrap Full Shurikane
description: A Wrap Full combined with a Shurikane.

name: Double Aerial Twist
description: An Aerial Twist with an extra twist, landing in complete stance.

name: Butterfly Kick Switch Hyperhook
description: A Butterfly Switch that lands in hyperhook.

name: Parafuso
description: A cheat set-up into a vertical Doubleleg. The earlier the legs get together for the doubleleg, the better the aesthetic.

name: Masterswipe
description: A Masterscoot that swipes over and lands in hyper, almost like a Cartwheel that takes off of the other foot.

name: Webster Hyperhook
description: A Webster that finishes with a hyperhook.

name: Double Full Shuriken Hyperhook Turbo
description: A Double Full Shuriken Hyperhook that lands in turbo (frontside that lands on both feet).

name: Feilong Snapu
description: An inverted Cheat Feilong with an extra 360° twist before landing.

name: Doubleleg X-Out
description: A Doubleleg that executed an X-Out at the peak of the jump. Created by Kim Do Nguyen.

name: Double Full Shuriken Hyperhook
description: A Double Full Shuriken that finishes with a hyperhook.

name: Corkscrew
description: A Gainer Flash with an extra rotation before landing - or a Back Full off of one leg.

name: Wrap Double Full Mega
description: A Wrap Double Full that lands in mega stance.

name: Triple Butterfly Twist
description: A Butterfly Twist with three twists.  First landed by John Vanek in July, 2013.

name: Boxcutter
description: A Corkscrew that finishes with a hyperhook.

name: Full Gumbi
description: A Full Twist that finishes with a Gumbi. Closely related to a 360 Backhandspring.

name: Sheep Shearer
description: A Double Corkscrew that finishes with a hyperhook.

name: Aerial Hook
description: An Aerial that finishes with a hook.

name: Wackknife Round
description: A Wackknife with a round kick executed before landing.

name: Gainer Hook
description: A Gainer Flash that finishes with an outside kick. Could be thought of as an inverted Skip Hook.

name: Rodeo Backflip
description: A Backflip with both arms grabbing the ankles and the back in an arched position.

name: Full Pike Round
description: A Full Pike that finishes with a round kick.

name: Pop 1260
description: The Pop 1260 starts in Frontside stance, leaves the ground off of both feet, rotates 1080° in the air, then lands and finishes with a round kick towards the target.

name: Aerial Helicoptero
description: A no-handed helicoptero.

name: Terada Grab
description: The Terada Grab can be done either as an Arabian variation or as a Sideflip variation. At the peak of the flip, the hook kick leg is grabbed with both hands and an axe/hook kick is executed from the peak of the flip to the landing. Created by Steve Terada

name: Corkscrew Doubleleg Hyperhook
description: A Corkscrew Doubleleg that finishes with a hyperhook.

name: Scoot
description: The Scoot is one of the easiest “setup” moves to learn – it is one of the first learned by beginners.

name: Cheat 720 Twist Hyperhook
description: A Cheat 720 Twist landed in hyper with a hook executed at the end. Can be thought of as a “laid back” Cheat 1080.

name: Sailor Moon
description: A Raiz where the right hand (assuming left twisting) is planted right before take-off. Like a Touchdown Raiz with the other hand.

name: Tak Rodeo Full
description: A Tak Full with a leg grab mid-flip.

name: Double Butterfly Twist Hyper
description: A Double Butterfly Twist that lands in hyper.

name: Cheat 1260 Hyper
description: A Cheat 1260 that lands on the kicking leg (inside leg) in Hyper.

name: Handcuff 360 Dive Roll
description: A 360 Dive Roll with the hands in the "handcuff" position.

name: Dragonfly Corkscrew Swipeknife
description: A Dragonfly Corkscrew that finishes with a Swipeknife.

name: Butterfly Kick Switch
description: A Butterfly Kick with a leg switch, landing on the opposite leg in complete.
